{"badges":["TM31","TM5","TM6"],"usefulItems":"baking paper, large serving bowl","id":"r146843","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-vXGr3fNVTD8\/XZMyNSomSUI\/AAAAAAAAah4\/DdIkZCQ__ok_ACO_UAFiztshRMcWqIoTgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_6xLc5lDDTJCV5SGv.png","title":"Pad Thai Noodles with Prawns","publishedAt":"2017-09-04T00:00:00Z","ingredients":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Ingredients"},{"content":"200 g dried rice noodles, flat, medium"},{"content":"water, boiling, for soaking"},{"content":"80 g roasted peanuts, unsalted,"},{"content":"3 garlic cloves"},{"content":"1 fresh red chilli, deseeded if desired"},{"content":"6 sprigs fresh coriander, roots and stems, reserving leaves for garnishing"},{"content":"20 g olive oil, plus extra for greasing"},{"content":"1 ½ Tbsp fish sauce"},{"content":"40 g lime juice (approx. 2-3 limes)"},{"content":"1 Tbsp tamarind paste"},{"content":"2 Tbsp soy sauce"},{"content":"¼ tsp shrimp paste"},{"content":"3 tsp palm sugar (approx. 1 cm cube), grated"},{"content":"2 medium eggs"},{"content":"500 g water"},{"content":"350 g raw prawns, peeled"},{"content":"70 g fresh bean sprouts, for garnishing"},{"content":"10 fresh chives, finely chopped, for garnishing"},{"content":"3 Tbsp crispy, fried shallots, for garnishing"},{"content":"1 lime, cut in wedges, for serving"}],"nutrition":{"protein":"29 g","fat":"17.5 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"17.3 g","calories":"1480 kJ \/ 352 kcal"},"preparations":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Preparation"},{"content":"Line both Varoma dish and tray with pieces of wet, well-wrung baking paper. Lightly grease baking paper on Varoma tray and set aside."},{"content":"Soak rice noodles in boiling water as per packet instructions. Drain noodles and place in a large serving bowl then cover to keep warm."},{"content":"Place peanuts in mixing bowl and chop <b>10 sec\/speed 4<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside. Rinse and dry mixing bowl."},{"content":"Place garlic, chilli and coriander roots and stems in mixing bowl then chop <b>3 sec\/speed 7<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add oil and cook <b>1 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>. Transfer half of herb mixture to Varoma dish and set aside."},{"content":"Add fish sauce, lime juice, tamarind paste, soy sauce, shrimp paste and palm sugar then mix <b>10 sec\/speed 5<b>. Transfer sauce to bowl with noodles and stir to coat noodles. Cover noodles again and set aside to keep warm."},{"content":"Without cleaning mixing bowl, place eggs in mixing bowl and beat <b>3 sec\/speed 5<b>. Transfer to lined Varoma tray, and spread evenly to create a thin layer. Carefully set Varoma tray aside."},{"content":"Place water in mixing bowl, place Varoma dish with herb mixture into position then weigh in prawns. Stir gently with spatula to combine."},{"content":"Carefully insert Varoma tray, then cover Varoma and steam <b>6 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Check prawns and transfer any cooked prawns to bowl with noodles."},{"content":"Cover Varoma then steam again <b>5-7 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b> until prawns are fully cooked and eggs are cooked as desired."},{"content":"Remove Varoma tray. Slice omelette into thin strips then add strips and prawns to bowl with noodles. Stir to combine."},{"content":"Top Pad Thai with bean sprouts, chives, reserved coriander leaves, shallots and reserved chopped peanuts. Serve immediately with lime wedges on the side."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Thermomix is great for Asian food – whether steaming prawns and an omelette as part of this Pad Thai or cooking rice for <i>Coconut Rice with Asian-inspired Pork and Eggs<\/i>, the results are always fantastic and flavourful.","Shrimp paste, also known as belachan, can be found in some supermarkets or Asian stores.","<strong>Vegetarian option<\/strong>: substitute prawns with 350 g mushrooms, sliced in step 8 and remove shrimp paste and fish sauce from recipe. Proceed as per recipe."],"basicInfo":["easy","25m","30m","4 portions"]}